Population Graphs on Vision Pro

Just got the Apple Vision Pro and started working on laying out using RealityKit. It is a bit different than SceneKit, but both better and more integrated with the features that I’ve come to love about modern Swift + SwiftUI development. I’m very excited.

First proof of concept for Population Graphs estimation and construction using Augmented Reality on the Apple Vision Pro.

I’ve very impressed, given that it has been just a few hours to make the transition from SceneKit legacy knowledge to jump right into RealityKit. This is going to be great.
